{"questionId":"12182","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question investigates the sum of sine and cosine functions</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 4\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> can be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\\,{\\text{cos}}(Bx + C) + D\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A{\\text{,}}\\,\\,B \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C{\\text{,}}\\,\\,D \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\pi&nbsp; < C \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + 12\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> can&nbsp;be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\\,{\\text{cos}}(Bx + C) + D\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A{\\text{,}}\\,\\,B \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C{\\text{,}}\\,\\,D \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\pi&nbsp; < C \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In general, the expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + b\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;can be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A\\,{\\text{cos}}(Bx + C) + D\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b{\\text{,}}\\,\\,A{\\text{,}}\\,\\,B \\in {\\mathbb{R}^ + }\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C{\\text{,}}\\,\\,D \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\pi&nbsp; < C \\leqslant \\pi \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The expression&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + b\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;can also be written in the form&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} \\left( {\\frac{a}{{\\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} }}{\\text{sin}}\\,x + \\frac{b}{{\\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} }}{\\text{cos}}\\,x} \\right)\">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msqrt>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>a</mi>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>b</mi>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </msqrt>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msqrt>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>a</mi>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>+</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>b</mi>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </msqrt>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{a}{{\\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} }} = {\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>a</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>b</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence prove your conjectures in part (e).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + b\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x = \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} \\left( {{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta \\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + {\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta \\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x} \\right)\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>θ</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>sin</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>θ</mi>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,x + b\\,{\\text{cos}}\\,x = \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} \\left( {{\\text{cos}}\\left( {x - \\theta } \\right)} \\right)\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cos</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cos</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>θ</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = \\sqrt {{a^2} + {b^2}} \">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>a</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>+</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>b</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B = 1\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"D = 0\">\n  <mi>D</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>And&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C =&nbsp; - \\theta \">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>So&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"C =&nbsp; - {\\text{arctan}}\\frac{a}{b}\">\n  <mi>C</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>arctan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>a</mi>\n    <mi>b</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12182","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.5g","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence prove your conjectures in part (e).","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.7—Circular functions: graphs, composites, transformations","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Compound angle identities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}